** 1. A Player has atleast one or  many Characters:**

  + A Player can own one or  multiple Characters.

  + A Character can only belong to one Player.


** 2. A Character belongs to only one Class:**

  + A Character is associated with one Class (e.g., Fighter, Wizard).

  + A Class can  be associated with many Characters.


** 3. A Character belongs to only one Race:**

  + A Character is associated with one Race (e.g., Human, Elf).

  + A Race can be associated with many Characters.


** 4. A Character participates in zero to many Events:**

  + A Character can be involved none or multiple Events.

  + An Event can involve many Characters.


** 5. A Player earns many Achievements:**

  + A Player can earn zero or multiple Achievements.

  + An Achievement can be earned by many Players.


** 6. A Character equips zero or many Items:**

  + A Character can equip multiple Items (e.g., weapons, armor).

  + An Item can be equipped by many Characters.


** 7. An NPC belongs to one Faction:**

  + An NPC (Non-Player Character) belongs to one Faction.

  + A Faction can have multiple NPCs.


** 8. An NPC can be in One or More Locations:**

  + An NPC (Non-Player Character) belongs to one Location.

  + A Location can have zero or more NPCs.


** 9. A NPC belongs to one Class:**

  + A NPC  belong belongs to one Class (e.g., Wizard, warrior).

  + A Class can classify multiple NPC.


** 10. A NPC belongs to one Race:**

  + A NPC belongs to one Race (e.g., Dragon, Goblin).

  + A Race can be assigned to many NPC.


** 11. A Monster is a subtype of a NPC:**

  + A Monster is an agressive NPC.

  + A monster correspoonds to an NPC, but not every NPC is a monster.


** 12. A Boss is a subtype of a Monster:**

  + A Boss is a special type of Monster that has unique attributes like fight phases or lair.

  + Each Boss corresponds to one Monster, but not every Monster is a Boss.


** 13. A Class teaches many Spells:**

  + A Class can teach multiple Spells (e.g., Wizards teach Fireball, Lightning Bolt).

  + A Spell can be taught by many Classes.


** 14. A Character can fight many Monsters:**

  + A Character can fight multiple Monsters.

  + A Monster can fight many Characters.


** 15. An Event involves many Characters:**

  + A Character can participate in multiple Events.

  + An Event can involve multiple Characters.

